  "label": "Seamline Stockroom",
  "description": "Seamline Stockroom occupies a windowless recess behind the Exchange’s stepped racks, its walls faced in matte basalt glass to suppress stray reflections. Narrow shelving bays and padded drawer-cabinets hold lens blanks, mirror-slag offcuts, and sealed vials of antistatic powders, each position indexed to the shop’s seam-line calibration scheme. A shallow dust-trench, lined with grounded fins, runs the perimeter to capture Lacrymara’s charged glass grit before it reaches stored optics. The air remains dry and copper-white in tone, sustained by baffled spill from the caged lightwells beyond.",
